The paper deals with the problem of computing the time-convex hull of a point set under the $L_p$ metric in the presence of a straight-line highway in the plane. This problem involves computational geometry (cs.CG) as it deals with geometric objects and their properties. The algorithm used in the paper is based on data structures (cs.DS) and the time complexity is analyzed using techniques from discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also involves graph theory (cs.GR) as it deals with finding shortest paths between points. Finally, the paper deals with optimization (cs.SI) as it aims to compute the time-convex hull in optimal time.
